main event: Multiple witnesses reported seeing a chlorotic shaped object, about the size of a nickel, move rapidly from north to south and then return north at a slow rate in Guadalupe, Arizona on October 25, 1966.
interesting points: The object was in the sky for about 15 minutes and was just above the horizon.
The witnesses included multiple family members - two brothers and a sister.
The investigating officer interviewed the witnesses and concluded the object was most likely a known aircraft or unusual atmospheric refraction.
The 17-year-old brother was also interviewed as a witness, and his appearance was considered particularly unreliable.
No physical evidence was indicated in the report.
sighted object: A chlorotic shaped object, about the size of a nickel
witnesses: Multiple family members, including two brothers and a sister
photographs: Yes, the report includes photographs, but none are visible in the provided image
